<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-23T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="590" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Wendelin, Eric C./86:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Straus</hi></persName>)<note n="57" xml:id="d590fn57">A somewhat similar telegram (No. 242, July 23,
                                    3 p.m.) was sent to the Ambassador in France for the Consul at
                                    Barcelona.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-23T16:00:00-04:00">July 23, 1936—4
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>243. Please convey following to Wendelin, Madrid: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Department highly gratified at the timeliness and
                                        thoroughness of your reports and steps you are taking to
                                        protect Americans in Madrid. You are authorized to draw for
                                        such reasonable funds as are necessary to purchase food,
                                        employ guards and provide any other equipment which you may
                                        require in connection with the care of American citizens and
                                        protection of Embassy.”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>